        <div><ol>
            <h3>Main life events:</h3>
            <li>Michael Jackson was born on August 29, 1958, in Gary, Indiana.</li>
            <li>He began performing at a young age with his brothers in the Jackson 5.</li>
            <li>In 1982, he released Thriller, which became the best-selling album of all time.</li>
            <li>His famous dance move, the “moonwalk,” debuted in 1983.</li>
            <li>He was called the “King of Pop” for his influence on music and performance.</li>
            <li>Michael Jackson died on June 25, 2009, in Los Angeles.</li>
        </ol></div>
        <div><ul>
            <h3>Main contributions:</h3>
            <li>Revolutionized music videos – with iconic works like Thriller, Beat It, and Billie Jean, 
                he turned music videos into mini-movies.</li>
            <li>Popularized the moonwalk – a dance move that became his signature and influenced generations of dancers.</li>
            <li>Broke racial barriers – he was the first Black artist to gain heavy rotation on MTV, opening doors for others.</li>
            <li>Humanitarian work – he supported many charities and raised millions for 
                causes like children’s health and disaster relief.</li>
        </ul></div>
